%% API request lifecycle (Phase 4). Authoritative for docs/04-System-Architecture.md §3. Two paths share one planner library.
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor C as Tenant client
    participant GW as api-gateway edge
    participant API as enrichment-api (modulith)
    participant ORCH as orchestrator+verify (modulith)
    participant COST as cost/billing (G4)
    participant Q as Kafka (async only)
    participant W as execution-engine workers
    participant PX as egress-proxy (SSRF)
    participant P as provider API
    participant DB as Postgres (RLS + provenance)

    Note over C,DB: SYNC path — single record (no queue; lowest p95)
    C->>GW: POST /enrich (JWT/mTLS)
    GW->>GW: authN/Z; tenant_id from principal (never body); rate-limit
    GW->>API: request + signed tenant context
    API->>ORCH: plan(record, fields, profile)
    ORCH->>ORCH: cache/preview → tiered identity → Pandora order + Thompson propose
    ORCH->>COST: reserve credits ≤ ceiling (G4) BEFORE any call
    COST-->>ORCH: reservation ok (else STOP)
    loop bounded parallel-prefix / cascade until SPRT stop | ceiling | timeout
        ORCH->>W: execute step (deadline, idempotency_key)
        W->>DB: idempotency ledger check (G2)
        alt cache/ledger hit
            DB-->>W: prior result (no paid call)
        else miss
            W->>PX: provider call (bounded G3)
            PX->>PX: allow-list + DNS-rebind-safe resolve; inject key
            PX->>P: HTTPS
            P-->>PX: result
            PX-->>W: normalized result
        end
        W->>W: calibrate → log-odds fuse → SPRT check
    end
    W->>DB: deterministic merge → write field_versions (value+confidence+PROV+cost+config-versions, G5)
    API-->>C: EnrichedRecord + provenance + cost ledger

    Note over C,DB: ASYNC path — batch/bulk (queue = back-pressure reservoir)
    C->>GW: POST /enrich/batch
    GW->>API: request + tenant context
    API->>DB: persist job + job_items (RLS)
    API->>Q: enqueue per-record items (partition=tenant_id, hash=record-id, idempotent)
    API-->>C: 202 job_id
    Q->>W: consume at per-(provider,key-pool) budget rate
    W->>PX: same pipeline as sync (shared planner lib)
    W->>DB: results + provenance
    W->>PX: webhook completion (idempotent, HMAC, via egress)
